This paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and involve the allocation of items among bidders, which can be modeled using data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of communication protocols to obtain efficient allocations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses a multi-party round-elimination technique, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
